{
  "texts": [
    "The results are shown in Table 2.",
    "Taking in consideration all the parameters described above, classifier Alpha presented a satisfactory performance evaluating a dataset never seen before by the model.",
    "This performance could be improved by increasing the quality as well as the amount of the data present in either the large general chemistry pre-training dataset or the much smaller NADES-specific fine-tuning dataset.",
    "The training time would increase in either case, but much more in the case of the large general chemistry dataset-possibly to the point that this strategy would be less attractive even for high end personal computers.",
    "Of these two possibilities to further improve the performance of the model, enriching the general-chemistry dataset would be far more costly and in-all-likelihood unnecessary, given the initial success of the model so far."
  ]
}